","text":"If I have walked with vanity, or if my foot hath hasted to deceit;","year":-1520},{"id":"reczb7SLJeG5f3PxT","ref":"Job.31.6","text":"Let me be weighed in an even balance, that God may know mine integrity.","year":-1520},{"id":"recz3fl8TlvgXDI9s","ref":"Job.31.7","text":"If my step hath turned out of the way, and mine heart walked after mine eyes, and if any blot hath cleaved to mine hands;","year":-1520},{"id":"reccIascd2f11yYUD","ref":"Job.31.8","text":"Then let me sow, and let another eat; yea, let my offspring be rooted out.","year":-1520}]}
